Key Match Events: The match between Morocco and Central African Republic will take place on October 12, 2024, at 20h local and central African time at the Stade d'Honneur d'Oujda. It will be 19h GMT and 21h in France.
Pre-Game Insights: Maroc is qualified for the CAN 2025 as the host country and has won their first two matches against Gabon (4-1) and Lesotho (1-0). Facing Central African Republic, the defense of the Lions of Atlas showed signs of fébrilité and it took until the 93rd minute for Brahim Diaz to score the winning goal against Lesotho. Key players such as Brahim Diaz, Noussair Mazraoui, and Hakim Ziyech are absent due to injury and health issues.
Post-Match Reflections: No post-match reflections are provided in the article.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will be broadcast on Arryadia in Morocco and beIN Sport 2 in France.
Others: The article also mentions that Lille's Osame Sahraoui and several new players may make their debuts for Morocco in the match. Central African Republic has started with a win against Lesotho (3-1), but lost to Gabon (2-0). They have a striker in form, Louis Mafouta, who has scored 5 goals in his last three appearances. The Central African Republic team is known for their ability to hold their own against stronger teams, with draws against Mali and Ghana in recent months, and a win against Nigeria in 2021.
